# License Agreement

Published: May 20, 2023

Source: [https://pruvious.com/license-agreement](https://pruvious.com/license-agreement)

## About this Agreement

Although Pruvious' source code is publicly available, it is **not free**. To use Pruvious in production, you must purchase a [license](https://pruvious.com/buy).

This End User License Agreement (the **"Agreement"**) is essential to the relationship between you and us. We recommend that you read this Agreement carefully before downloading, installing, or using Pruvious.

If you do not agree to this agreement, please do not download, install, or use Pruvious. By installing or using Pruvious, you agree to be bound by the terms of this agreement, which you have read and understood.

## Definitions

Before we get started with the conditions of the Agreement, let's define the terms that will be used throughout it:

When we use the term **"You"**, we are referring to the licensee. The licensee is the individual or company that has downloaded and/or installed Pruvious for either a Development Installation or Private Installation. If Pruvious is used for a Public Site, the licensee is the individual or company that has purchased the Pruvious license. If you are working on a client project and have purchased the Pruvious license for your client, then you (and _not_ the client) are considered the licensee.

When we use the terms **"We"/"Us"/"Our"**, we are referring to the licensor, the Vivid Binaries GmbH. For more information about our company, please visit [https://vividbinaries.com](https://vividbinaries.com).

A **"Project"** is a single Pruvious project defined by its domain name and root directory (e.g. `https://sub.example.com` or `https://example.com/example/`). Each (sub)domain and root directory is a separate Project if they are not related to each other. For example, two websites that use the same code base but represent different subjects are two separate Projects. Conversely, a website with translations across many (sub)domains or root directories is still considered one Project.

A **"Development Installation"** is a Project that is installed purely for the purposes of development and client preview. It should only be accessible by a restricted number of users. Examples of restricted access include: on a personal computer, on a server in a network with restricted access, or when protecting a staging website with a password that only a restricted number of users know.

A **"Private Installation"** refers to a Project that is installed solely for personal use. It should only be accessible to You and Your family.

A **"Public Site"** refers to a Project that is neither a Development Installation nor a Private Installation.

The **"Source Code"** is defined as the contents of all files provided with Pruvious that make it work. This includes all code files as well as related image and other media files, but is not limited to these.

Every time You see one of these capitalized terms in the following text, it refers to the meaning that has been explained above.

## Usage for a Public Site

To install or use Pruvious on a Public Site, You need to purchase a paid [license](https://pruvious.com/buy).

Since Pruvious is software and intangible, We don't sell it as such. Instead, this agreement grants a license for each purchase to install and use a single instance of Pruvious on a **specific website**. Additional Pruvious licenses must be purchased to install and use Pruvious on **additional websites**.

The license is **non-exclusive** (meaning that We can issue a license to others) and **generally non-transferable** (meaning that the purchaser is the licensee).

Upon request, We will **transfer** a license to anyone who is allowed to purchase Pruvious licenses under the law and this agreement. The new licensee will assume all rights and obligations under this agreement from You at the moment We confirm the license transfer.

We can also **reassign** a license to a different website domain and root directory of Your choice, provided that You confirm that the previous website is no longer in operation and will not be operated with the same license in the future.

If You need to transfer Your Pruvious license to another individual or company (for example, to Your client or a new agency) or reassign it to a different Project, please contact Us directly at [support@pruvious.com](mailto:support@pruvious.com).

A license is valid for all versions of all Pruvious releases.

## Order Process

Our order process is conducted by Our online reseller [Paddle.com](https://www.paddle.com/). Paddle.com is the Merchant of Record for all Our orders. Paddle provides all customer service inquiries and handles returns.

## Free Licenses

Pruvious can be used **for free in the following cases**. Please note that the restrictions and all other clauses of this Agreement also apply to free licenses. You may especially _not_ alter or circumvent the licensing features.

### Usage for a Development Installation

We believe that it should be possible to test and evaluate software before having to purchase a license. Also, We understand that a web project first needs to be built in a protected environment before it can be published. Therefore, installing and using Pruvious on a personal computer (like a desktop PC, notebook, or tablet) or server for a Development Installation is **free** for as long as You need. The usage of Pruvious in production (with the intention to handle production data or content) is _never_ considered a Development Installation, even in internal apps or systems.

### Usage for a Private Installation

You may also install and use Pruvious for **free** in Private Installations as long as they are not accessible by anyone except You and Your family. Our definition of a Private Installation allows the following use cases:

- Private sites for personal use, for example:
  - Apps for You personally (like a personal diary)
  - Apps for You as a freelancer (like a bookkeeping, invoicing, or project management app)
  - Apps for Your family (like a private photo gallery)
- Experimental local Pruvious setups for Your personal use (for example to try out Pruvious features)

However, the following use cases are _not_ covered and need a **paid license**:

- Intranets for companies, authorities, or organizations, no matter if on a local or public server
- (Internal) apps for teams or entire companies, authorities, or organizations
- Websites that are accessible by the public, even for personal/non-commercial purposes
- Use of Pruvious as a local CMS for a static or headless site without a license for the frontend domain(s)

## Restrictions

### Legal Restrictions

You may only use Pruvious in a manner that complies with any and all **applicable laws** in the jurisdictions in which You use Pruvious. Please respect all applicable restrictions concerning **privacy and intellectual property rights**.

Making Copies
You may make **copies of Pruvious** in any machine-readable form solely for the **following purposes**, provided that You reproduce Pruvious in its original form and with all proprietary notices on the copy:

- when deploying a Project to a server,
- when developing a Project on a personal computer or server,
- when working on code contributions to Pruvious, or
- as a backup.

You may _not_ reproduce Pruvious or its Source Code, in whole or in part, for **any other purpose**.

### Modification of the Source Code

You may **alter, modify, or extend the Source Code** for Your own use or with the intention to contribute Your changes back to Pruvious. You may also **commission a third party** to perform those modifications for You. However, You may not:

- **alter or circumvent the licensing features**, including (but not limited to) the license validation and payment prompts, or
- **resell, redistribute, or transfer** the modified or derivative version.

Please note that We **can't provide technical support** for modified or derivative versions of the Source Code.

### Your Relationship to Third Parties

You are generally _not_ allowed to **sell, assign, license, disclose, distribute, or otherwise transfer or make available** Pruvious or its Source Code, in whole or in part, in any form to any third parties.

The following cases are exempted from this restriction:

- Pruvious licenses may be transferred to a new licensee by requesting the transfer from Us.
- You may create Projects for third parties (e.g., as an agency or freelancer for a client). Together with this Project, You may bill Your client for the used Pruvious license. You may also include the license price in a flat rate. Please note that the licensee in both of these cases is still You unless You request to transfer the license to Your client. If Your price exceeds the price You paid to Us, You need to give Your client the option to purchase the license directly from Us.
- You may make Pruvious available to customers via a Software-as-a-Service (SaaS) offering, provided You ensure that each Project has a valid Pruvious license purchased either by You or Your customer. If multiple customers share a Project, each customer needs at least one license. Your offering _must not_ appear to be provided or officially endorsed by Us.
- You may make a Pruvious installation available to employees or partners of You or Your Project client. You may also disclose and distribute Pruvious’ Source Code to Your client together with the source code of the Project You created for them.
- You may disclose the Source Code to individuals or companies that are involved in the development or operation of Your Project (e.g., agencies, design or development freelancers, hosting providers, or administrators).

E.g., the following cases are explicitly **_not_ allowed**:

- Selling, licensing, or distributing a new product based on Pruvious that modifies or hides Pruvious’ identity as a Content Management System (CMS)
- Forking Pruvious and selling the modified version
- Buying licenses in bulk and reselling them in Your shop
- Bundling or including Pruvious’ Source Code in the publication and/or distribution of a Project’s source code or a (free or paid) theme or plugin

### Disallowed Uses

The following uses of Pruvious are _not_ covered by this Agreement and will result in the termination of the license:

- Use of Pruvious for websites that contain misinformation, hate speech, or discriminating content based on age, gender, gender identity, race, sexuality, religion, nationality, serious illnesses, or disabilities, no matter who authored this content. Misinformation is defined as content that is false or misleading and may lead to significant risk of physical or societal harm.
- Use of Pruvious by **companies or individuals who**:
  - lobby for, promote, derive a majority of income from, or are significantly invested in:
    - the production of tobacco or weapons,
    - any prison or jail operated for profit,
    - any action or facility that supports or contributes to:
      - gambling, adversely addictive behaviors, or
      - deforestation.
  - lobby against, or derive a majority of income from actions that discourage or frustrate:
    - peace,
    - access to the rights set out in the Universal Declaration of Human Rights and the Convention on the Rights of the Child,
    - peaceful assembly and association (including worker associations),
    - a safe environment or action to curtail the use of fossil fuels or to prevent climate change, or
    - democratic processes.

### Other Restrictions

You may also _not_:

- **extract parts of the Source Code** for use in other programs or projects (unless the code file in question is explicitly licensed under the terms of the MIT license) or
- **remove or alter any proprietary notices** on Pruvious.

## Technical Support

Technical support is **provided as described on Our website** at [https://pruvious.com/support](https://pruvious.com/support). **No representations or guarantees** are made regarding the response time in which support questions are answered; however, We will do Our best to respond quickly. We reserve the right to **limit technical support for free licenses**.

## Refund Policy

We offer a **14-day**, money-back refund policy if Pruvious didn't work out for Your project. If You need a refund, please get in touch directly at [support@pruvious.com](mailto:support@pruvious.com).

